cGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe89f1506" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Musk is=
 asking for a delay</a>. The judge might not want to delay the trial to thr=
ow in a grab bag of miscellaneous new issues that no one has mentioned befo=
re, but=C2=A0Musk=E2=80=99s (and Zatko=E2=80=99s) argument is that no one h=
as mentioned them because Twitter kept them secret, and if he=E2=80=99s rig=
ht that they are serious issues then it seems unfair to him to ignore them.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As I said yesterday, you could have two readin=
gs of what is going on here. One is that Musk has been playing cynical game=
s to get out of his binding agreement to buy Twitter, and it has not been g=
oing very well for him, and this =E2=80=94 scouring=C2=A0Zatko=E2=80=99s co=
mplaint for more excuses to get out of the deal =E2=80=94=C2=A0is a new cyn=
ical game that he is playing. On that reading, you should not be very sympa=
thetic to him, or delay the trial, or let him out of the deal. The other re=
ading is that Musk has been playing cynical games to get out of his binding=
 agreement to buy Twitter, and it has not been going very well for him, and=
 Zatko=E2=80=99s complaint is, by sheer coincidence, a=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0<=
/em>reason for him to get out of the deal. It=E2=80=99s just his, and our, =
weird dumb luck that while he was flailing around trying to back out of thi=
s deal, it came out that Twitter is doing a bunch of frauds that should let=
 him out of the deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have my own view about which is more likely.=
=C2=A0But my point here is that Zatko=E2=80=99s complaint has enormous, unu=
sual=C2=A0<em>leverage</em>. In the ordinary course, a complaint like this =
might generate hearings and investigations and lawsuits, but there would be=
 reasonable settlements, and=C2=A0its impact on Twitter and its shareholder=
s would ultimately be pretty limited. But because of the pending Musk deal =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0and Musk=E2=80=99s desire to get out of that deal, and his w=
illingness to litigate everything to the death to do so =E2=80=94=C2=A0this=
 complaint could cost Twitter and its shareholders, you know, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28895329.263565/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMTEvdGhlLXByaWNlLW9mLW=
5vdC1idXlpbmctdHdpdHRlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwODMwMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtP=
WVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA4MzAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWdu=
PW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8fbdb4eb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  $20 billion</a=
>, or whatever the difference is between Musk=E2=80=99s price of $54.20 per=
 share and what Twitter would be worth without him.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Zatko=E2=80=99s complaint came out, <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28895329.263565/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cud2FzaGluZ3RvbnBvc3QuY29tL3RlY2hub2xvZ3kvaW50ZXJhY3RpdmUvMjAyMi90d2=
l0dGVyLXdoaXN0bGVibG93ZXItc2VjLXNwYW0v/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC564345e4" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> a Twitter spokesperson said</a> that he =E2=80=9Cappears to be oppo=
rtunistically seeking to inflict harm on Twitter, its customers, and its sh=
areholders,=E2=80=9D and there is an important sense in which that is true.=
 In the normal case, if you read Zatko=E2=80=99s complaint and assumed that=
 everything in it was (1) true and (2) as bad as Zatko thinks it is, you wo=
uld not expect it to cost Twitter=C2=A0<em>twenty billion dollars=C2=A0</em=
>to clean it up. But because of the Musk situation, that is a possibility. =
The timing gives his complaint an unusual power to hurt Twitter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously one possible outcome is something li=
ke =E2=80=9Cokay, in the real world, this complaint is at the absolute maxi=
mum a $1 billion problem, so Twitter will knock $1 billion off the purchase=
 price and Musk will close the deal at $53 per share.=E2=80=9D If Musk stil=
l wanted Twitter,=C2=A0and if this complaint was truly news to him, that is=
 the sort of compromise that you=E2=80=99d expect them to reach. But Musk w=
as already fighting to get out of the deal entirely, and there's no real ch=
ance of a compromise like that. Musk=E2=80=99s incentives are to make Zatko=
=E2=80=99s claims seem existential for Twitter, because that=E2=80=99s his =
path out of the deal.=C2=A0</p>
